d the challenge of the growth of online stores most of the group’s customers including brands and department stores are struggling brands are under significant pressure of reduction in costs and inventory while looking at shorter lead time and lower cost of production as a manufacturer investment in vertical setup smart factory and performance fabric could be a possible solution to these challenges the group is investing into the group’s “future factory” in cebu with focus on innovation automation and integrating waterless fabric dyeing technology to shorten the group’s delivery lead time and enhance the group’s competitiveness going forward with the joining of new directors with innovative ideas and different business views in february  the management is now reassessing and reviewing the existing operations and simultaneously exploring new business opportunities for the apparel manufacturing the group has invested in a printing factory in the philippines which can shorten the group’s delivery lead time and hence enhance the group’s competitiveness in certain print related apparel production the board also believes that after the disposal of noncore businesses and focusing on its core businesses the company will be gaining momentum and moving towards a promising future the group will unceasingly search for various investments and business opportunities that fit in the group’s new business strategy so that the group can bring benefits to the company for its sustainable growth and strive to increase the return of the group’s shareholders information from the financial statements of listed companies last update  related news luen thai hk buys  remaining stake in sweater mfg subsidiary with usm luen thai tan cho lung succeeds as ceo luen thai hk annual net profit usm final div us cents luen thai changes ceo luen thai offeror receives acceptances for  stakes public float below min requirement   sitemap back to the top ▲ aastockscom  mainpage products market  hk indices  